@node OVERVIEW "PROGRAM OVERVIEW"
        Three years ago I decieded that I was very tired of decompressing files
        one at a time and having to create directories to put each one into.
        Since most compressed files on the Amiga use 'lha' as their compression
        routine with a few using 'dms', I decided to create an interface
        that would use these routines and most others without me having
        to sit at the computer. This is how ABFDIK was born. It has come
        a long way since Version 1.0 but always has remained VERY STABLE.
        It has internal settings to use with LHA, LX, DMS, LZX, UNZIP, DECRUNCH and
        PPACK. Included is an editor for adding more definations for other
        decompression programs.

        This is not just another interface but one of the most
        reliable and versitle interfaces for decompression there is.

        Drop me an @{"Email" link "email"} if you like it.
 @endnode

