@node  INSTALL  "HOW TO INSTALL ABFDIK"

     AUTOMATIC INSTALLATION:

        USE THE INSTALLERS, THER ARE 2. ONE IS FOR THE PROGRAM WHILE THE OTHER
        INSTALL THE PD DECOMPRESSION AND VARIOUS OTHER PROGRAMS THAT ARE INCLUDED.

     YOU CAN READ THE INSTALLATION FILES WITH A TEXT VIEWER TO SEE WHERE EVERYTHING
     WENT.


@endnode

@node "USAGE" "HOW TO USE ABFDIK"
USING THE PROGRAM

  This program uses buttons, menus and keys.

  Start by using the buttons and the menus.

  To see the keys or menus available press the RIGHT 'ALT' OR LEFT 'ALT' KEY,
  this toggles a help screen.

  MUSIC FUNCTION IS NOT ON THE KEY VIEWER IN THIS VERSION BUT IT WORKS.
  TO PLAY A MOD LOAD IT USING THE MENU. TO STOP THE MUSIC JUST GO TO THE
  MENU AGAIN AND SELECT PLAY MUSIC AND IT WILL STOP.

  To toggle the program from front to back and back to front use the
  left Amiga Key + A. This is very useful when using the CLI or other
  programs.

  The program will run while the key help screen is showing if you so
  desired.

  A SOURCE & DESTINATION MUST BE CHOSEN BEFORE MOST OF THE ROUTINES
  IN THIS PROGRAM WILL OPERATE. BEFORE DECOMPRESSION CAN TAKE PLACE
  YOU MUST SELECT THE 'USER PROGRAM' FROM THE MENU.
       E.G. LHA OR LX OR DMS ETC., DEPENDING ON THE TYPE OF FILES
            YOU ARE GOING TO DECOMPRESS. LHA AND LX WILL DECOMPRESS
            FILES WITH THE EXTENSIONS .LHA OR LZH WHICH IS 99.9%
            OF ALL FILES OUT THERE.

  While it is not absolutely necessary it is best to set a default
  Destination and Source. This can be done by clicking on menu item 7 or
  pressing F7. Once set it will automatically come up when the program
  is loaded. You always have the option of using a different temporary
  settings using the buttons marked Change Source Directory and Change
  Destination Directory. Keys S and D will also work in place of these
  buttons. The file containing this info will must be kept in the 'SYS:T'
  directory of your harddrive.

  Now that we have set the default Source and Destination let us continue.

  Buttons:

  Use the mouse to click them.

  Extreme upper left box with red dot in center - EXIT PROGRAM

  Automatic Operation - Just press this button and all files from your
  source will be copied to your destination.

  Files that don't have extensions or have extensions that your user
  program can't handle will not be copied, but will remain in your source directory.
  You may use the menu item # 6 'Copy programs to ' by clicking on it
  or pressing F6.


  Manual Operation - Easy to use, decompresses one file at a time.
  Click on file to decompress, then choose a destination and type a '*' on
  the bottom line of the file requestor and the file will be decompressed
  to that location.

  Create Icons For Drawers - The default is yes. You will notice the
  button is pressed when the program starts. All files of the selected type
  will be decompressed to drawers in the destination directory that
  have icons.
  The rest of the files will remain in the SOURCE directory.

  If you deselect this button all the above files will be copied to drawers
  that have no icons.

  It is always a good idea to set the workbench 'Window Menu' to Show All
  Files when viewing your directories directly on the workbench for
  decompression purposes.

  Change Destination Directory - Pressing this button will allow you to
  select a different destination directory for this session. IT WILL NOT
  CHANGE YOUR DEFAULT SETTING.

  Change Source Directory - Pressing this button will allow you to
  select a different source directory for this session. IT WILL NOT
  CHANGE YOUR DEFAULT SETTING.

  Button Help - Toggles Button and Menu Help. When on point at a button
  and its function is revealed in a help screen, same for menu items.

  Copy Empty Drawer Icon To Source - you MUST have the empty draw icon
  in your source directory. This button was added just to make the coping
  a little easier.

  See Directories - A directory gadget to veiw ANY directory. It is not
  functional except for viewing.

  Reset - Resets program to default settings.

  Delete Files - Deletes files from any directory 1 at a time.

  Delete Contents of Directory - Please be VERY CAREFUL as this is a
  very powerful routine and can even wipe out a whole partation on a
  hard drive if that partation is selected. IT ALWAYS DELETES from the
  HIGHEST directory selected down to all the contents of sub directories.

  HELP ME - Loads this file into the program for reading

  Count - Gives a count of all 'COMPRESSED' programs to be decompressed
          that match the USER program parameters.

  Eyeball - Pressing this button allows you to view the file info
  on all files that were compressed into the master file if you have a
  viewer for that user program loaded in the C directory or have defined
  a command for viewing.


  LIST MENU:

      THE FUNCTION OF THE LIST MENU (MENU 3), IS TO CREATE, READ, PRINT, COPY
      OR DELETE A FILE CONTAINING A LIST OF ALL THE PROGRAMS IN YOUR SOURCE
      DIRECTORY. IT IS HANDY SINCE SOME OF THE FILES MIGHT BE TEXT OR
      PICTURES AND YOU MAY WANT TO CHECK THIS LIST TO DECIDE IF YOU WANT TO
      MOVE OR COPY ANYTHING BEFORE DELETING THIS DIRECTORY AFTER DECOMPRESSING
      YOUR FILES.

        1. CREATE FILE - CREATES THE LIST FILE IN YOUR RAM: DIRECTORY
        2. READ FILE - BRINGS UP A TEXT READER WITH THE LIST FILE LOADED IN
           FOR READING.
        3. PRINT LIST - PRINTS THE LIST FILE IF IT EXISTS IN RAM:
        4. COPY LIST - COPIES THE LIST FILE TO YOUR DESTINATION DIRECTORY, IF
           THE LIST FILE EXISTS IN RAM:
        5. DELETE LIST - DELETES LIST FILE FROM RAM: IF IT EXISTS. ON EXITING
           THE PROGRAM THIS HAPPENS ANYWAY.




@endnode

@node KEYS "KEYS, BUTTONS AND MENUS"
KEYS AND MENUS

  LIST OF KEY MACROS

  F1 = CLI  F2 = READ TEXT FILE  F3 = READ RAM DIRECTORY  F4 = TOGGLE LOG
  F5 = TOGGLE PRINTER  F6 = COPY UTILITY  F7 = SET DEFAULT SOURCE & DEST
  F8 = UNSET THE SOURCE & DEST  F9 = MAXIUM SPACE TOGGLE  F10 = ABOUT

  M = MANUAL OPERATION 1 FILE DECOMPRESSED AT A TIME FROM SOURCE DIRECTORY
  A = AUTOMATIC OPERATION ALL FILES DECOMPRESSED IN SOURCE DIRECTORY
  S = SET SOURCE DIRECTORY
  D = SET DESTINATION DIRECTORY
  I = TOGGLE ICON CREATION BUTTON
  H = BUTTON HELP
  R = RESET SOURCE AND DESTINATION TO DEFAULT
  U = SHOWS ALL INFO ON USER PROGRAMS
  C = ENTER COPY FILE MODE
  P = PRINT A FILE
  X = ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
  $ = UNDOCUMENTED KEY TO LOAD A TRACKER MODULE - NOT FOR STOPPING MUSIC
  LEFT ALT OR RIGHT ALT = TOGGLE F KEY AND MENU SCREENS
  LEFT AMIGA + A TOGGLE PROGRAM TO BACK AND FRONT

 *note WHEN TURNING ON THE LOG, ANY ATTEMPT TO READ THE FILE USING F2 OR
       MENU ITEM 'READ TEXT FILE' WILL TURN OFF THE LOG. IF THE LOG IS
       TURNED ON AGAIN IT WILL BE OVERWRITTEN.
       THE AUTOLOG_FILE REMAINS IN RAM: UNTIL DELETED

  WARNING - USING THE MAXIUM SPACE OPTION WITH MIXED FILE TYPES MIGHT
            CAUSE THE ERASURE OF ALL TYPE NOT MATCHING THE SELECTED
            EXTENSION TYPE. E.G. IF YOU SELECT THE USER PROGRAM 'LHA'
            ANY EXTENSIONS OTHER THAN .LHA OR .LZH MIGHT CAUSE ERASURE.


@endnode

